In a medium bowl, break up tuna with a fork. Stir in beans and 3 tablespoons of the onion. In a 1-cup glass measure, stir together dressing, basil, and garlic. Pour over tuna and toss. Line four plates with lettuce. Spoon tuna into center of each plate. Add olives, cucumber, and onion evenly to each plate. Alternate egg and tomato around tuna on each plate. Add salt and pepper to taste. Serve with more dressing to taste.